<TITLE> 3 abducted in Rangamati </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, Nov 9 (bdnews24.com)  Unidentified assailants abducted three men on Monday, including a local Union Parishad member, in Barkal Upazila, Rangamati, locals and relatives said. The three were identified as Pathar Moni Chakma, UP member of Bhushon Chhora-4, Joy Kumar Chakma, 40, and Singh Moni Chakma, 42. All abductees were from Shukari Pata village in Barkal Upazila, said locals. They said a gang of abductors took the three men away at gun point to Kaptai Lake, one and a half kilometres from Barkal Upazila. Police confirmed the abductions. Khairul Bashar, sub-inspector of Barkal Police Station, told bdnews24.com, however, that they were yet to receive any complaint on behalf of the abductees' families. Locals and relatives of the abductees blamed United People's Democratic Front for the kidnapping. Local UPDF leader Maichaeel Chakma has rejected the allegation. He said UPDF were not involved with any extortion or abduction. "Our enemies make false allegations against us to tarnish our image,". bdn
